Dialogue: 10,0:00:09.03,0:00:11.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Inoue Platoon,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:11.66,0:00:14.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,deployed to Burma during the final stages of the Pacific War,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:14.78,0:00:17.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,met the end of the war there.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:18.49,0:00:23.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After the surrender, the captain ordered\N one of their soldiers, Private Mizushima,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:23.04,0:00:26.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to go to Triangle Mountain and negotiate with a Japanese unit
Dialogue: 10,0:00:26.14,0:00:29.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,that had holed up there\N and kept on fighting.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:29.46,0:00:33.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Mizushima took his beloved harp with him.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:34.75,0:00:38.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,During the war, he had mastered the Burmese harp.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:38.22,0:00:42.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His playing could lift the morale\N of the entire battalion immediately.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:42.81,0:00:45.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He was loved by everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:46.96,0:00:52.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A few days later, the Inoue Platoon was transferred to a POW camp in Mudon.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:52.90,0:00:58.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But even several months later, \NMizushima hadn't joined them there.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:13.47,0:01:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that Mizushima?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:15.83,0:01:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Impossible. It can't be.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:17.92,0:01:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But he looks just like him.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:22.33,0:01:26.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Burmese monk looked exactly like Mizushima.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:27.62,0:01:32.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,But if it {\i0}was{\i1} Mizushima, \Nwhy didn't he say a word to us?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:32.55,0:01:37.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,No, rather, why would he shave his head\N and pretend to be a monk?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.63,0:01:41.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,That was the question on everyone's mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:42.27,0:01:44.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,I knew it wasn't Mizushima.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:45.36,0:01:47.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,Mizushima must've died on Triangle Mountain.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:48.28,0:01:50.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,That was the only answer\N that made sense.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.35,0:02:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What brings you here so soon?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.14,0:02:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I had stuff to trade, but the battalion next door was away.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:05.90,0:02:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, look at that parrot!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.20,0:02:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like the one that monk on the bridge had.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:12.22,0:02:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that one was green too.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:15.15,0:02:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you met that traveling monk too?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.55,0:02:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny, do you know him?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.58,0:02:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked like a distinguished monk.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:23.51,0:02:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the younger brother\N of the bird that monk has.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:26.66,0:02:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband caught\N three birds in the woods.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:30.04,0:02:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when the monk approached him,\N asking for directions.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:33.64,0:02:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband gave him one of the parrots for his blessing. {?? not sure what she says especially with that kansai ben but it's something about praying for him}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:36.79,0:02:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny, would you sell that bird to us?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:39.99,0:02:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be glad to, but what are you going to do with it?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:45.51,0:02:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is to thank you for everything you've told us so far.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.18,0:02:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thanks a bunch!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:50.62,0:02:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can teach him Burmese, or Japanese, or whatever you like!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:10.51,0:03:12.46,Top,,0,0,0,,Take a rest!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.06,0:03:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did the Captain buy that parrot?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.58,0:03:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,As a souvenir, maybe.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.61,0:03:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll teach it to sing to replace you,\N since you're so bad!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.08,0:03:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,"Hey, Mizushima,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.23,0:03:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,come home to Japan with us."
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.24,0:03:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,"Hey, Mizushima, come home to Japan with us..."
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.10,0:03:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you say it.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.03,0:03:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mizushima...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.14,0:03:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Good boy.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.59,0:03:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"Come home to Japan with us."
Dialogue: 10,0:03:53.88,0:03:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Come home. Come.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.18,0:04:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no use. It's too hard for him.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.40,0:04:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, why are you teaching the bird these words?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.01,0:04:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We're already eager enough to go home,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.22,0:04:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're shaking the platoon's morale. {??? nc what's that odoremasu, also nc why they care about morale if they're not going to be doing any more fighting?}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.52,0:04:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't do this.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:22.83,0:04:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.59,0:04:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But for some reason,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.43,0:04:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get over the feeling\N that Mizushima is still coming back to us.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:31.46,0:04:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That Burmese monk we saw on the bridge
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.18,0:04:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,might have actually been Mizushima in disguise.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.48,0:04:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time we see him,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.84,0:04:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I plan to put this bird on his shoulder.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.71,0:04:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's Mizushima, the bird will tell him what we want to say,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.95,0:04:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and he'll probably give us some answer.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:49.96,0:04:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But if he still says nothing, \Nwe'll know it's not him.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.13,0:04:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when I'll give up.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:57.64,0:05:02.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,Several days later, there was another strange incident.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.91,0:05:07.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,We heard a harp that sounded exactly like Mizushima's.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.83,0:05:12.33,Song,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{荒城の月 / koujonotsuki again, 4:46 in previous episode; copying the translation from there}In spring, a cherry blossom viewing party is held in the high tower
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.33,0:05:24.95,Song,,0,0,0,,The moon's shadow shines\N on the cups we exchange
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.95,0:05:37.48,Song,,0,0,0,,Shining through pine tree branches\N that have lasted for a thousand years
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.48,0:05:50.38,Song,,0,0,0,,Where is the glory of the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.38,0:05:53.76,Song,,0,0,0,,In autumn, the camp{\fscx300}- {Aki jin-ei no shimo no iro}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:03.64,0:06:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Mizushima's harp!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.72,0:06:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's him!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.46,0:06:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming from the forest!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:10.85,0:06:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's coming from inside that statue!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.59,0:06:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.04,0:06:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's odd. Are you sure it came from here?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:24.75,0:06:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's solid stone. There's no way in.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.78,0:06:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Found it! Here's the entrance!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.48,0:06:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima, are you in there?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.79,0:06:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We know it's you, Mizushima!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.50,0:06:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're in there, answer us!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.04,0:06:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Say something!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.92,0:06:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima! Answer!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.92,0:06:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.75,0:06:45.94,Top,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.94,0:06:47.92,Top,,0,0,0,,Stop! Stop doing that!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:49.33,0:06:50.68,Top,,0,0,0,,Go back to work!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.15,0:06:55.00,Top,,0,0,0,,Hurry! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.26,0:07:03.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,Then, at the end of that summer, \Nan order came in I was not expecting.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.34,0:07:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, they're sending us back! \NWe're all going back to Japan, people!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.18,0:07:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.23,0:07:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All the POWs in Mudon\N are being sent home!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.05,0:07:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We leave in three days!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.80,0:07:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going home?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.25,0:07:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.16,0:07:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The Captain told me! He just talked to the British commander.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.04,0:07:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray! {yatta}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.32,0:07:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.71,0:07:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mizushima,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.26,0:07:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,come home to Japan with us.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.84,0:07:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mizushima,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.82,0:07:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,come home to Japan with us.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.58,0:07:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. We should go along with the Captain's plan
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.69,0:07:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and give that parrot to the monk\N one of these days.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:47.78,0:07:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If he really is Mizushima...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.20,0:07:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he'll come back to us!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.56,0:07:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we can all go home together.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.02,0:08:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are only three days left.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.03,0:08:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How are we going to give the parrot to that monk?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:04.42,0:08:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't just go search\N for him on our own.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.07,0:08:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! I know!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.82,0:08:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.99,0:08:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll sing every morning, \Nas loud as we can.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.37,0:08:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima will definitely hear it and come!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.89,0:08:23.06,Song,,0,0,0,,{traditional song "hakone mountains"; full lyrics: 箱根の山は　天下の険\N函谷関も　物ならず\N万丈の山　千仞の谷\N前に聳え　後に支う\N雲は山をめぐり　霧は谷をとざす\N昼なお闇らき　杉の並木\N羊腸の小径は　苔滑らか; translation from https://www.mamalisa.com/?p=836&t=es&c=85 ; in our fansub of 12 sets of eyes I translated this song as "The mountains of Hakone are\N as swords beneath the heavens; Kankokukan cannot begin to compare" lol}The Hakone Mountains are\N the steepest place in the world
Dialogue: 10,0:08:23.06,0:08:27.23,Song,,0,0,0,,More so than Kankokukan,\Nthere's no comparison
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.23,0:08:30.97,Song,,0,0,0,,Sky-high mountains with a bottomless ravine
Dialogue: 10,0:08:30.97,0:08:35.30,Song,,0,0,0,,Rising in the front, shored up in the rear
Dialogue: 10,0:08:35.30,0:08:39.43,Song,,0,0,0,,Clouds are on the mountains,\N fog circles, and the dales fill up
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.43,0:08:47.68,Song,,0,0,0,,Even during the day,\N the rows of cedar trees are dark
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.68,0:08:50.32,Song,,0,0,0,,The narrow path of moss...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:29.99,0:08:34.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,Two days passed, and we sang until our throats were raw.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.19,0:08:36.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,That Burmese monk might be
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.29,0:08:38.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,among the audience gathered outside the camp.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:38.82,0:08:44.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,No, we knew for sure that\N he'd come once he heard us sing.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.51,0:08:50.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,But it turned out that all our work was for nothing.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.32,0:08:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it wouldn't work.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:52.04,0:08:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My throat's killing me.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.52,0:08:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Whose great idea was this?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:56.87,0:09:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations! I'm very happy that you boys get to go home.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.90,0:09:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.82,0:09:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure helped us out a lot.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.81,0:09:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I get home, I'll tell my mother all about you.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.08,0:09:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's something to remember me by.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.35,0:09:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.82,0:09:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and me.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.28,0:09:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, thanks, everyone!\N I'm sure I ain't ever forgetting you either.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.82,0:09:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny, could you give this to that monk
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.71,0:09:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we've talked about before,\N the one who keeps a bird? {???? no idea where that "owns 2-3 birds" came from, we only saw him keeping one, and even that was gifted to him}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.60,0:09:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but that's impossible.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:26.21,0:09:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a traveling monk, so I don't have any way of knowing where he is.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:29.60,0:09:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Please! We're leaving tomorrow!\N I'm sure you can find him!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:32.71,0:09:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.68,0:09:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny, please!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:35.29,0:09:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. I'll see that he gets it, then. \NDontcha worry about a thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.75,0:09:41.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,Then, later that evening...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.72,0:09:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He's here! He's here! He's here!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.64,0:09:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Who's here?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:46.92,0:09:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima's here!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.23,0:09:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.26,0:09:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I mean that monk. \NHe's right outside the fence.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.10,0:10:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the bridge monk, all right.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.86,0:10:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He has both parrots.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.10,0:10:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny must have found him.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.57,0:10:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a good look. \NIs he really Mizushima?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.81,0:10:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Come home to Japan with us.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:32.63,0:10:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's not him, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:35.02,0:10:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's sing anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.75,0:10:48.41,Song,,0,0,0,,{same song as two times before}Mid pleasures and palaces though we may roam
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.41,0:10:58.88,Song,,0,0,0,,Be it ever so humble, there's no place like home
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.88,0:11:09.68,Song,,0,0,0,,A charm from the skies seems to hallow us there
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.68,0:11:21.06,Song,,0,0,0,,Which seek thro' the world, is ne'er met elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.06,0:11:30.80,Song,,0,0,0,,Home! Home! Sweet, sweet home!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.80,0:11:36.08,Song,,0,0,0,,There's no place like home
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.08,0:11:41.87,Song,,0,0,0,,There's no place like home!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:45.87,0:11:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:46.90,0:11:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God! You're back!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.60,0:11:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going home tomorrow!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:50.55,0:11:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back with us! Mizushima!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.96,0:11:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.06,0:11:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.90,0:11:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.52,0:11:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Come home!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.19,0:11:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.66,0:12:21.68,Note,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,500)}Note: Mizushima is playing {\i1}Tabidachi no Hi ni{\i0}, also known as the "Japanese Graduation Chorus Song," a symbol of an immediate and inevitable parting. {I know this looks silly but I think this note is important for understanding the message here; https://www.lyricslayers.com/ai-kawashima/1800090/}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.47,0:13:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.28,0:13:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.08,0:13:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mizushima!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.56,0:13:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back! {????? guess}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:06.72,0:13:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:08.90,0:13:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.03,0:13:15.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,We left the POW camp the next day.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.83,0:13:18.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,A transport ship picked us up near Mudon
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.47,0:13:20.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,and departed toward our motherland of Japan. {?? nc what's that kakou, but mudon is not a coastal town so they had to reach the coast first}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.11,0:13:35.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,As we left camp, the peddling granny came running up.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.75,0:13:40.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,She gave us a letter and a parrot.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.12,0:13:42.77,Thought,,0,0,0,,Naturally, they were from the monk.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.77,0:13:47.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,I mean, the letter was\N from Mizushima for us.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.10,0:13:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everyone here? \NI'm going to read the letter now.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.25,0:13:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this letter's supposed to explain
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.20,0:14:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,why Mizushima couldn't come back with us.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:05.37,0:14:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"Captain, my friends, you don't know how much I've missed you.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:13.37,0:14:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no idea how much\N I'd wanted to come back to you,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.67,0:14:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to work, talk, and sing with all of you,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.99,0:14:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and how much I longed to return to Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:21.10,0:14:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No words can express that.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:23.50,0:14:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But I cannot just go home now."
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.68,0:14:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, when I left all of you, \NI set out for Triangle Mountain.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.31,0:14:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My mission was to persuade the Japanese forces
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.56,0:14:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,who continued to resist there.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.56,0:14:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, I couldn't complete that mission,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.24,0:14:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was badly wounded in the process.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.06,0:14:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,An old Burmese monk found me. \NHe saved my life.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.78,0:15:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But all I wanted was to return\N to my platoon, no matter what.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.91,0:15:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the only thing I thought about.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.27,0:15:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In desperation, I walked relentlessly to Mudon.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.50,0:15:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But along the way,\N I saw something terrible.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.18,0:15:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,These are Japanese.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.54,0:17:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I couldn't hope to bury more\N of those bleached bones on my own.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:03.97,0:17:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So I hurried on to Mudon\N as fast as I could.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:20.76,0:17:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll finally see you all tomorrow!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.79,0:17:52.34,Top,,0,0,0,,Why are you playing so early in the morning?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.38,0:17:54.55,Top,,0,0,0,,For practice.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:54.55,0:17:57.34,Top,,0,0,0,,The British soldiers pay me to play for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.99,0:18:24.08,Top,,0,0,0,,And thanks be to God, who delivers me through our Lord Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.08,0:18:25.89,Top,,0,0,0,,So then, my dear brothers...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.21,0:18:34.89,Top,,0,0,0,,{???}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.89,0:18:36.05,Top,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:25.89,0:18:27.83,Top,,0,0,0,,They're from the British hospital.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.83,0:18:31.19,Top,,0,0,0,,More of the wounded Japanese soldiers died this morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.84,0:18:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I remembered all those bones
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.50,0:19:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of my compatriots, scattered across Burma,\N exposed to the elements.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.69,0:19:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I couldn't just abandon them like that and return to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.66,0:19:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So I turned around and went north again.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.56,0:19:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And on my way back, on the bridge,\N I passed by you all.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:31.33,0:19:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't imagine how I felt, \Nseeing you back then.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:34.90,0:19:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But I knew that I had to do what was right. {lit: made up my mind to return [to the bodies]}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.91,0:19:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't rejoin you, \Nand I couldn't tell you who I was.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.24,0:19:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing I could do was keep walking north, silently.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:55.30,0:19:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I can't go back home yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.82,0:20:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima must have\N said that every day.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:04.59,0:20:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So even the parrot managed\N to remember it.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.63,0:20:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I climbed the mountains, crossed the rivers,\N and returned to the dead. {??}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.18,0:20:21.16,Song,,0,0,0,,{same song as 3 times before that, this time with second verse too; 埴生の宿も わが宿\N玉の装い 羨まじ\Nのどかなりや 春の空\N花はあるじ 鳥は友\Nおお わが宿よ\N楽しとも たのもしや\N\N書読む窓も わが窓\N瑠璃の床も 羨まじ\N清らかなりや 秋の夜半\N月はあるじ 虫は友\Nおお わが窓よ\N楽しとも たのもしや}'Mid pleasures and palaces though we may roam
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.16,0:20:32.35,Song,,0,0,0,,Be it ever so humble, there's no place like home
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.35,0:20:42.84,Song,,0,0,0,,A charm from the skies seems to hallow us there
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.23,0:20:55.05,Song,,0,0,0,,Which, seek thro' the world, is ne'er met elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.05,0:21:05.52,Song,,0,0,0,,Home, home, sweet, sweet home
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.52,0:21:10.91,Song,,0,0,0,,There's no place like home
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.91,0:21:16.54,Song,,0,0,0,,There's no place like home
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.54,0:21:27.67,Song,,0,0,0,,An exile from home, splendor dazzles in vain
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.67,0:21:39.04,Song,,0,0,0,,Oh, give me my lowly thatch'd cottage again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.04,0:21:49.62,Song,,0,0,0,,The birds singing gaily that came at my call
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.62,0:22:01.04,Song,,0,0,0,,Give me them with the peace of mind dearer than all
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.04,0:22:11.04,Song,,0,0,0,,Home, home, sweet, sweet home
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.04,0:22:25.28,Song,,0,0,0,,There's no place like home\NThere's no place like home
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.83,0:20:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,As I worked to bury\N the drenched corpses,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.09,0:20:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I was tormented by uneasy misgivings.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.59,0:20:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Why must such misery exist in this world?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:23.46,0:20:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why must such insanity exist?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:27.60,0:20:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The Captain said we'd all return to Japan, without leaving anyone behind,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:31.48,0:20:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to work together to rebuild our homeland.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.23,0:20:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, his words are\N echoing in my heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:38.43,0:20:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But once I'd seen my dead compatriots\N left there to rot,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:42.84,0:20:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I couldn't abandon them.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.39,0:20:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I've decided to remain in this land\N to create a place of rest
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.47,0:20:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for the souls of hundreds of thousands\N of my fallen compatriots.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.75,0:20:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how many years it'll take, but when I'm done,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:58.14,0:21:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll finally be able to come home.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:00.38,0:21:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, probably not even then.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:03.94,0:21:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll probably spend my entire life here.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:07.18,0:21:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this is my fate.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:11.33,0:21:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The other day, \Nwhen I was inside the statue,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:14.72,0:21:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard you calling out to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:16.80,0:21:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted so much to run out \Nand greet you all.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.88,0:21:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima, are you in there?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:21.26,0:21:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're in there, answer us!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.72,0:21:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima! Answer!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:24.38,0:21:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:36.88,0:21:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So today I forgot my oath and came to play my harp for you. {?? dunno what's heiso here}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.42,0:21:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how many farewell words I write, they will never be enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:47.04,0:21:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I am staying in Burma\N to wander everywhere,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.36,0:21:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,from the snow-covered mountains to the seashores,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:53.75,0:21:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,shining under the Southern Cross.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:56.44,0:22:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I can't stand the loneliness anymore, I'll play my harp again.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:03.08,0:22:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't thank you enough\N for all your friendship and loyalty.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:07.62,0:22:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I sincerely wish you \Nall the best in your endeavors.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:11.62,0:22:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima Yasuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.05,0:22:37.91,Song,,0,0,0,,I write a letter to my loved one
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.61,0:22:44.83,Song,,0,0,0,,I write and tear it, tear it, and write again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.83,0:22:51.38,Song,,0,0,0,,I throw the rolled up paper at the window
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.38,0:22:58.55,Song,,0,0,0,,It's raining outside, just like the tears on my cheeks
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.66,0:23:06.43,Song,,0,0,0,,Life is a sea, youth is a boat
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.43,0:23:13.50,Song,,0,0,0,,My love, please come and save me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.50,0:23:15.92,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.81,0:23:19.03,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.67,0:23:27.18,Song,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm sinking
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.18,0:23:36.60,Song,,0,0,0,,Not a single star in sight, in the sea of ​​sadness
